## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 5.1: Implement Backend Logic and API for Application Backup**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for backup initiation
  - [ ] Implement backup process as background task
  - [ ] Define data to be included in backup
  - [ ] Create backup manifest file
  - [ ] Implement backup archive creation and storage
  - [ ] Add API response and feedback mechanisms
  - [ ] Ensure database integrity during backup
  - Success criteria: Asynchronous backup process with manifest creation
  - Dependencies: Epic 1, Epic 2 (Admin Routes)

- [ ] **Story 5.1.5: Implement API Endpoints for Managing Backup Files**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for listing backup files
  - [ ] Implement backup file download endpoint
  - [ ] Add backup file deletion endpoint
  - [ ] Ensure proper security for all endpoints
  - Success criteria: Complete API for backup file management
  - Dependencies: Story 5.1

- [ ] **Story 5.2: Implement Backend Logic and API for Application Restore**
  - [ ] Create API endpoint for restore initiation
  - [ ] Implement backup validation in background task
  - [ ] Add manifest reading functionality
  - [ ] Create database restoration and migration process
  - [ ] Implement asset file restoration
  - [ ] Add API response and feedback mechanisms
  - Success criteria: Reliable restore process with proper order and error handling
  - Dependencies: Story 5.1

- [ ] **Story 5.3: Develop Admin UI for Backup, Restore, and Backup File Management**
  - [ ] Create system operations admin page
  - [ ] Implement backup file listing and management UI
  - [ ] Add UI for initiating new backups
  - [ ] Create restore from backup UI with warnings
  - [ ] Implement asynchronous feedback for operations
  - Success criteria: Intuitive UI for backup and restore operations
  - Dependencies: Stories 5.1, 5.1.5, 5.2

- [ ] **Story 5.4: Implement Basic System Statistics Display**
  - [ ] Create statistics section in admin dashboard
  - [ ] Implement backend API for statistics
  - [ ] Add UI for displaying user, group, and URL counts
  - Success criteria: Admin dashboard displays key system statistics
  - Dependencies: Epic 2 (Admin Dashboard)

- [ ] **Story 5.5: Implement Basic User Activity Tracking Log**
  - [ ] Create ActivityLog Prisma model
  - [ ] Implement backend logging service
  - [ ] Add logging for key system actions
  - [ ] Create admin UI for viewing activity log
  - [ ] Implement backend API for log retrieval
  - Success criteria: Comprehensive activity tracking with admin UI
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 5.6: Implement Configurable Log Retention Policy**
  - [ ] Update SystemSetting schema with logRetentionDays
  - [ ] Create admin UI for log retention configuration
  - [ ] Implement backend API for policy management
  - [ ] Add automated log pruning scheduled task
  - [ ] Create manual log pruning trigger
  - Success criteria: Configurable log retention with automated and manual pruning
  - Dependencies: Story 5.5

## Affected Components

- Database schema (ActivityLog, SystemSetting)
- Admin API endpoints for system operations
- Admin UI for backup, restore, and monitoring
- Background processing for async operations
- Scheduled tasks for maintenance

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema)
- Epic 2 (Admin Dashboard)
- node-cron for scheduled tasks
- formidable/archiver/unzipper for file handling
- Prisma ORM

## Technical Considerations

- Backup and restore operations must be asynchronous
- Database migrations must be handled properly during restore
- Log pruning must not impact system performance
- Manifest format must be consistent and validated
- Security for backup/restore operations is critical

